tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Opened the season with a T7 finish at the Freedom 55 Financial Open, missing out on a playoff by two shots...Shot four rounds in the 60s to T5 at the National Capital Open...Concluded season 34th on Order of Merit.

2014: Missed earning status at the British Columbia Q-School...Finished T21 on a sponsor's exemption at the Freedom 55 Financial Open and Monday qualified for the Syncrude Boreal Open, where he shot weekend rounds of 65-69 to T8...As one of the top three non-members on the Order of Merit midway through the season, earned status for the remainder of the season...As one of the top three non-members on the Order of Merit midway through the season, earned status for the remainder of the season...Two weeks after a disqualification at the Forces and Families Open, carded four under-par rounds (69-68-69-66) at The Great Waterway Open to earn his second top-10 of the campaign...Two starts later, posted rounds of 67-70 on the weekend at the Cape Breton Classic to T3, two shots out of a Mark Silvers-Matt Harmon playoff won by Silvers.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA T was T3rd in 2014 at the Cape Breton Celtic Classic presented by PC Financial.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks 24th in Scoring Average (Actual) on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA TOUR Canada.
